 United States plasmid DNA manufacturing for cell and gene therapy market size was valued at USD 0.54 billion in 2025. The market is projected to grow from USD 0.58 billion in 2026 to USD 1.04 billion by 2034, exhibiting a CAGR of 8.9% during the forecast period.

Plasmid DNA manufacturing involves the production of circular double‑stranded DNA vectors that serve as delivery vehicles for therapeutic genes in cell‑based and gene‑editing applications. These vectors are engineered through bacterial fermentation, purification, endotoxin removal, and rigorous quality control to meet regulatory standards for clinical use.

